parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various issues, including flickering interior lights, alarm malfunction, battery drain, and even fires, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or property damage.

The failure of the alternator and charging system can cause the battery to drain, leading to stalling, inability to start the vehicle, and loss of essential functions, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Wiring harness and grounding issues can cause electrical system failures, including flickering lights, battery drain, and even fires, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
